\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104iwi1665702603846.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iwi1665702603846.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iwi1665702603846.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"iwi1665702603846\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      trigger validate (Entity)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">System trigger for validating entity occurrences.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__section_w616ab1b7b1_w617ab1b7_w618ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__table_d14342e1_d14343e1_d14344e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Declaration:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">trigger validate</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Applies to:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uqv1665702561461.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uqv1665702561461.html\" title=\"An Entity is an abstract data type that defines a logical data aggregation and its associated default characteristics and behavior. It may be mapped to a table in a DBMS, and is most frequently used to represent the application data, but it can also represent transient data, a collection of controls, or constant data.\">Entity</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activation:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activated during explicit or validation:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__li_d44372e1_d44373e1_d44374e1\">Explicitly, during the processing of one of the validation statements (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validate</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validateocc</span>).\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__li_d44375e1_d44376e1_d44377e1\">Implicitly, during the processing of a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">store</span> statement.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__li_d44378e1_d44379e1_d44380e1\">Implicitly, after declarative checks and, in forms, before the leaveModified trigger is activated.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default behavior:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">If no ProcScript is present in this trigger,\n                        there is no action; both <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>,\n                           <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occvalidation</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occcheck</span> are\n                        set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Behavior upon completion:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n If <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> is less than zero, validation is considered to have failed and the entity-level error trigger is activated.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__section_w619ab1b7b3_w620ab1b7_w621ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d439261e165\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__p_d116633e1_d116634e1_d116635e1\">The validate trigger defines the procedural checks that are done to validate a modified occurrence.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__p_d116636e1_d116637e1_d116638e1\">Validation is performed only if the occurrence is marked as modified (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span> is 1) and still requires validation (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occvalidation</span> is 1), or if <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occcheck</span> is 1.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__p_d116639e1_d116640e1_d116641e1\">Because the validation statements (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validatefield</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validatekey</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validateocc</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validate</span>) activate the validation triggers (validate and validateKey), these statements should be used with caution within the validation triggers.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__section_vw5_y1j_fcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d439261e201\">Example: Validate Occurrence</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">In the following example, the fields CITY and ZIP_CODE are\n               cross-checked with each other before the occurrence is considered valid:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"iwi1665702603846__pre_fjg_z1j_fcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger validate ; of Entity\n if ( CITY = \"\" &amp; ZIP_CODE = \"\") ;city &amp; zip are missing\n $status = -1 ;oops!\n elseif ( CITY = \"\" &amp; ZIP_CODE !=\"\") ;city is blank, but zip is present\n activate \"LOCATOR\".FILL_CITY_FROM_ZIP(CITY, ZIP_CODE)\n elseif ( CITY != \"\" &amp; ZIP_CODE = \"\") ;city is present, but zip isn't\n $status = -2 ;can't help here\n else ;both city and zip are present\n activate \"LOCATOR\".MATCH_CITY_ZIP(CITY, ZIP_CODE)\n endif\nreturn ($status) ;return what we've got\nend; validate</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lcw1665702604012.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ProcScript for Data Validation</a><p>ProcScript instructions can be used to explicitly validate data, set validation conditions, check modification and validation status, and handle errors.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xmm1665702603717.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger leaveModified</a><p>Trigger that handles processing after the user moves to another occurrence in a form, after having modified the original occurrence.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvb1665703130778.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger store</a><p>Trigger that responds to a request to save (store) the data.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ugh1665703129789.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger validate (Field)</a><p>System trigger that defines the procedural checks to validate a modified field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/frh1665703129863.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger validateKey</a><p>System trigger that defines the procedural checks to validate a modified primary or candidate key.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528741\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528741\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "trigger validate (Entity) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 trigger validate (Entity) System trigger for validating entity occurrences. Declaration: trigger validate Applies to: Entity Activation: Activated during explicit or validation: Explicitly, during the processing of one of the validation statements ( validate or validateocc ). Implicitly, during the processing of a store statement. Implicitly, after declarative checks and, in forms, before the leaveModified trigger is activated. Default behavior: If no ProcScript is present in this trigger, there is no action; both $status , $occvalidation , and $occcheck are set to 0 . Behavior upon completion: If $status is less than zero, validation is considered to have failed and the entity-level error trigger is activated. Description The validate trigger defines the procedural checks that are done to validate a modified occurrence. Validation is performed only if the occurrence is marked as modified ( $occmod is 1) and still requires validation ( $occvalidation is 1), or if $occcheck is 1. Because the validation statements ( validatefield , validatekey , validateocc , and validate ) activate the validation triggers (validate and validateKey), these statements should be used with caution within the validation triggers. Example: Validate Occurrence In the following example, the fields CITY and ZIP_CODE are cross-checked with each other before the occurrence is considered valid: trigger validate ; of Entity if ( CITY = \"\" & ZIP_CODE = \"\") ;city & zip are missing $status = -1 ;oops! elseif ( CITY = \"\" & ZIP_CODE !=\"\") ;city is blank, but zip is present activate \"LOCATOR\".FILL_CITY_FROM_ZIP(CITY, ZIP_CODE) elseif ( CITY != \"\" & ZIP_CODE = \"\") ;city is present, but zip isn't $status = -2 ;can't help here else ;both city and zip are present activate \"LOCATOR\".MATCH_CITY_ZIP(CITY, ZIP_CODE) endif return ($status) ;return what we've got end; validate Copy Related Links ProcScript for Data Validation ProcScript instructions can be used to explicitly validate data, set validation conditions, check modification and validation status, and handle errors. trigger leaveModified Trigger that handles processing after the user moves to another occurrence in a form, after having modified the original occurrence. trigger store Trigger that responds to a request to save (store) the data. trigger validate (Field) System trigger that defines the procedural checks to validate a modified field. trigger validateKey System trigger that defines the procedural checks to validate a modified primary or candidate key. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}